Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:02.14,English,,0,0,0,,You may have heard of an event horizon
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:02.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你也许听说过事件视界
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.14,0:00:06.28,English,,0,0,0,,the boundary beyond which not even light can escape a black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.14,0:00:06.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在黑洞视界内即使光也不能逃脱
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.28,0:00:08.87,English,,0,0,0,,This is a very interesting surface to think about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.28,0:00:08.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是一个相当有趣的界面
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.87,0:00:12.96,English,,0,0,0,,but i want to talk to you about the other boundary around a black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.87,0:00:12.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是今天我要向你介绍黑洞中的另一个界面
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.96,0:00:15.20,English,,0,0,0,,it's known as a stationary limit surface
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.96,0:00:15.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们称之为静界
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.20,0:00:17.14,English,,0,0,0,,In order for this boundary to be noticeable
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.20,0:00:17.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为了让这个界面比较明显
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.52,0:00:19.36,English,,0,0,0,,our black hole has to be spinning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.52,0:00:19.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们的黑洞需要有一定的自旋
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.36,0:00:23.58,English,,0,0,0,,so let's imagine that we're looking at it from above or from one of the poles
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.36,0:00:23.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,想象我们从上方或者转轴方向看去
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.58,0:00:28.66,English,,0,0,0,,the spinning of the black hole actually ends up dragging the space time surrounding it
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.58,0:00:28.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,黑洞的自旋将会拖曳周围的时空
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.66,0:00:34.48,English,,0,0,0,,it if any object even a photon of light enters this region known as the ergosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.66,0:00:34.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,任何物体 即使是光子 只要进入到能层
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.48,0:00:37.83,English,,0,0,0,,the region between the event horizon and the stationary limit surface
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.48,0:00:37.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,即事件视界和静界之间的区域
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.83,0:00:39.84,English,,0,0,0,,then for somebody looking from far away
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.83,0:00:39.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在远处的某人看来
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.84,0:00:44.39,English,,0,0,0,,the object will always appear to rotate in the same direction as the black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.84,0:00:44.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个物体总是顺着黑洞的方向旋转
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.39,0:00:47.84,English,,0,0,0,,even if it was going the other way before entering the ergosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.39,0:00:47.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,即使它是从相反的方向进入能层的
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.84,0:00:51.16,English,,0,0,0,, that's because the space time in which this object exists
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.84,0:00:51.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是因为这个物体所处的时空
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.16,0:00:54.78,English,,0,0,0,,is literally being dragged around with the rotation of the black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.16,0:00:54.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,被黑洞的旋转扭曲了
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.78,0:00:59.60,English,,0,0,0,,that's why this effect is known as frame dragging
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.78,0:00:59.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是为什么这个效应被称作参考系拖拽
